A 27 year old man was arrested in his home in Ottery in connection with the murder of Stellenbosch University student Robyn Pearce. According to reports the suspect appears to be a construction worker at the Beach Court apartment building in Sea Point where Pearce s body was found. When the incident occurred construction and repair work were being carried out on the building. The body of 20-year-old Pearce was found in an apartment block on 2 December with multiple stab wounds. SAPS spokesperson Andre Traut confirmed that the suspect is due to make a court appearance in the Cape Town Magistrate court on Monday for murder chargers. Robyn Pearce was buried in Durban on Saturday.-TNA Reporter